The article discusses the importance of National Foster Care Month in recognizing the needs and potential of children and youth in foster care. It emphasizes the significance of providing these individuals with a safe and loving home, as well as the support they require to grow into healthy and productive adults. The article mentions the efforts made by the government, such as increasing funding for adoption and foster care assistance programs, implementing the Fostering Connections to Success and Increasing Adoptions Act, and ensuring Medicaid coverage for former foster youth. It encourages the involvement of federal, state, and local government agencies, communities, and individuals in supporting young people in foster care and honoring the adults who work on their behalf. The article concludes with a proclamation by President Barack Obama, designating May 2010 as National Foster Care Month.